The paper deals with the model-checking problem of Dynamic Pushdown Networks (DPNs) against CARET formulas, which involves temporal logic and multithreaded programs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves reductions and decidability results, which are common in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the detection of concurrent malware, which could fall under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with pushdown systems, which could be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
